====Equipment====
The basic equipment of the above mentioned vehicles are obligatory and are minimal requirements:

* Basic [[First Aid]] kit.
* Dressings and Bandages
* [[Gurney]] and blankets
* Flexible stretcher, also called a Reeves stretcher.
* Rigid or collapsible transport chair, also called a stair chair in the United States
* Mobile [[medical ventilator]]
* Basic diagnostic equipment, like blood-pressure cuffs.
* Portable [[defibrillator]]
Depending on the type of the vehicle, there are numerous items which have to be on the ambulance, among them are:
* An [[Electrocardiogram|ECG monitor]]
* Rescue equipment
* Immobilization equipment like [[Cervical collar]]s or [[Long spine board|spine boards]]
* Equipment for [[intravenous therapy]]

Additionally, several different kinds of drugs are found on an Ambulance, typically a selection of [[analgesic]]s, [[anaesthetic]]s, [[cardiac|cardiac stimulants]], substances for [[circulatory|circulatory problems]] and [[antidotes]].
[[Narcotics]] are not widely carried on ambulances. Usually only the physician will carry a small amount of [[Morphine]], [[Fentanyl]] or [[List of drugs: Pi#piri-pirn|Piritramide]] and closely guard them.
